  "prompt": "How do I configure a universal remote?",
  "response": "To configure a universal remote, follow these general steps:\n\n1. Find the correct code for your device\n- Check the remote's manual\n- Look online for device codes\n- Use the remote's code search function\n\n2. Preparation\n- Insert fresh batteries\n- Make sure the device you're programming is plugged in\n- Have the device turned on\n\n3. Programming methods (varies by remote):\n\nMethod 1: Direct Code Entry\n- Press and hold the device button (TV, DVD, etc.)\n- Enter the code using number buttons\n- Wait for the device to turn off/lights to flash\n\nMethod 2: Code Search\n- Press and hold the device button\n- Press the power button repeatedly until the device turns off\n- Press the device button to save the code\n\nMethod 3: Auto-Code Search\n- Press and hold the device button\n- Press the power button\n- Remote will cycle through codes automatically\n- Stop when your device turns off\n\n4. Test the remote\n- Check if volume, power, and other functions work correctly\n- If not, repeat the programming process\n\n5. Additional tips\n- Some remotes require specific programming sequences\n- Consult the user manual for detailed instructions specific to your remote",
